##Five days after my father died, my mother died

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Shen Wendi, Wen Xiaoxiao, _ the _ paper _

On February 15, Wuhan welcomed the first snow of the year of the Gengzi rat.

That morning, Li Yue (not her real name)'s father died after more than two hours of futile attempts to revive him after suffering from new coronary pneumonia.

A day earlier, Li Yue, recovering from new crown pneumonia, braved the cold, dragging her frail body on a bike-sharing trip to Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital, where she became the first person to voluntarily donate plasma. Holding a glimmer of hope, she wanted to use their own plasma to save his father.

Hope is dead. For more than a month, Ms. Li has had nightmares: first, her mother's condition worsened after her cancer was terminal; then, after the outbreak, she and her father were diagnosed with new crown pneumonia; after her father left, her mother's treatment stalled again, finally gone..

Now Li Yue alone guarding the empty house, very much hope that this memory was also isolated dust-laden.

A family of three

This was supposed to be a happy family of three.

Li Yue's father, 67, is retired and prefers to stay at home, fiddling with cameras and fixing pictures to watch movies. Her mother, 63, loves food and enjoys square dancing, drumming and performing with friends.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Yue's mother and father, pictured

Their only daughter, Li Yue, has excelled since she was a child. After graduating from Peking University, she moved to the UK in 2016 to work and has a bright future.

When she first arrived in the UK, she was not alone. Li and her mother would video chat and talk about each other's lives and experiences over an eight hour time difference.

But starting in late 2016, Li slowly found that her mother often refused to answer video calls, smart voice. When I asked, my mother said she was recuperating in a hot spring and the signal was not good.

Feeling Strange Li Yue began to ask around relatives, but got the reply is all right, Li Yue after want to come, think it should be the mother gave them a call, don't let themselves worry.

But the mother's condition was discovered after all.

In the summer of 2017, Li learned after returning from vacation that her mother had advanced rectal cancer and had undergone a round of chemotherapy and surgery. Li Yue moment collapsed, she can not imagine, how her mother is hiding her alone to carry the pain down.

Li Yue's father at first and Li Yue the same reaction, muddled for several days, in the mother's support and encouragement before slowly accept the reality.

For the next three years, the couple's hobbies stopped. Father Daily Rush home and between the hospital, to the mother send food, accompany, scrub the body. Because rectal cancer patients are special, a stoma is opened for excretion, and the father is responsible for the replacement and cleaning.

After her mother fell ill, Li Yue originally wanted to return home to accompany her, but her mother did not allow her to do so, to develop abroad is her daughter's expectations. Even after Li Yue returned home, her mother did not want her to come to the hospital, she did not want her daughter to see the pain of oncology patients.

From then on, the mother and daughter began to video every day, at first the mother will say a lot of words, but as the severity of the disease, she can talk for less and less time, the picture of the mother is thinner and thinner.

"My mother is a very aggressive person, even if it hurts, she does not want to cause trouble. Some patients Groan and call a nurse. She holds the pillow tightly in her hand, frowning, holding it in. Ask Her if it hurts. She nods, but doesn't say anything,"said Li Yue.

In December 2019, after a third round of treatment failed, the ailing mother was unable to eat and began to survive on nutritional injections. But after a while, she wanted to stop and spend her last days with her family. She was taking 45 milligrams of morphine a day and a powerful painkiller, but the cancer was still killing her.

One day in the video, his parents told Li that his mother had written a statement not to resuscitate him: After stopping the injection, if there is any emergency treatment, I hope the doctor will not take any emergency measures.

Ms. Li said she could not accept the decision, but only when she saw first-hand how painful her mother was, did she realize that she was not living for herself, but for herself and her father.

But before the family could make a final decision to stop the injection, new pneumonia broke out. Another shock hit the family, and the mother had to carry on, waiting for the people she loved and loved most.

Infection

On January 9,2020, her mother suddenly asked if Li Yue could return to China. Li Yue heard that her mother might not have much time, and flew back to Wuhan from London the next day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Yue's plane ticket, photo by interviewee

When she returned home, she was told she had to be accompanied 24 hours a day. One is the care of life, the other is the mother's emotional comfort. A nurse told her in secret that her mother was in such a state of pain that she feared she would commit suicide.

Without hesitation, Li Yueyi stayed in the hospital ward 24 hours a day. His father came by bus at noon to deliver meals, and then returned home by bus at 7 or 8 pm.

At this point, the family had no idea how contagious the new coronavirus was. After returning home, Ms. Li said, she only wore a mask outdoors, did not protect herself in the hospital, and did not disinfect herself when she returned home.

It wasn't until Jan. 19 that Ms. Li noticed that the doctors and nurses in the ward began wearing two layers of face masks, the N95 inside and the surgical mask outside, and that the staff members, who usually didn't wear hats, started wearing two layers of hats and tucking in their hair.

A doctor called Li Yue out and told her family to put on their masks while they were in the ward, saying the situation outside was much more serious than expected.

From this point on, Li Yue really vigilant up, snatched a box of masks. But the most worrying thing has happened.

For the next few days, Li Yue had an itch in her throat and wanted to cough. At noon on January 25, she began to have a fever and a slight cough. She thought that she would wait a day to see if it was just a dry hospital environment.

But when she came back the next day, she went to the fever clinic with her father. Her CT showed patches of ground glass in her lungs, as did his, and it matched the new type of pneumonia. But without a nucleic acid test, they could not be diagnosed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
CT findings of fathers (left) and Li Yue (right) , pictured

Since Jan. 27, when Ms. Li and her father could no longer stay in the hospital with her mother and had to be quarantined at home, they hired a nurse aunt to take care of her. But his mother said a person can, go to the toilet will not trouble others, hard to support themselves to go.

After the father has been thinking about his mother, mentioned her crying, he was frustrated that he could not be with his lover, only through the phone contact.

More to his Chagrin and self-blame, is this time to let his daughter back, infected with the virus.

After several twists and turns, my father and Li Yue were admitted to Wuhan No. 8 Hospital on January 30 and 31, respectively, in two wards on different floors.

In fact, Li Yue in the hospital before the fever, after the hospital she asked someone to buy a Gamma Globulin for himself and his father on, plus anti-viral and anti-inflammatory drugs, her condition soon stabilized.

But the father was not well. He has had a fever since the early hours of January 31st, with a temperature of 39.5 degrees Celsius. Due to the large number of patients, he did not receive any more treatment, but only managed to keep up with the fever medicine he brought with him.

Doctors also told Li Yue, at this time the Eighth Hospital is only temporary placement of patients, even nucleic acid testing can not do. My father's floor had lost three patients in one day.

The doctor also told Li Yue that the new crown pneumonia needs to rely on its own immunity to fight, but in the hospital, breakfast and lunch are dumplings, and in the evening, rice and winter melon, and no one at home can bring them rice, at this point, Li Yue even had regrets about being admitted to the hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The pictures of breakfast (left) and lunch (right) taken by Li Yue during her hospital stay on February 1 are from the "Selfie" and were released with the consent of the interviewees

She had to supplement herself and her father with take-out food, and she was never able to see him because of the isolation. It wasn't until February 3 that she learned that her father, who had been diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia, needed to be transferred to Golden Pond Hospital.

As she was loading him into the ambulance, she found him weak, but she didn't think it would be goodbye.
Plasma that can't wait

Li Yue's father was transferred to the gold and Silver Pool Hospital after a gradual improvement, can self-breathing, oxygen saturation increased. But the doctor told her that the old man's inflammation has not been able to eliminate, has been a fever. During the meal, Li Yue would call his father to encourage him to eat.

On Feb. 5, Li Yue, who was diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia, was also transferred to Jinyintan Hospital, where a second CT scan showed that her lungs had improved significantly. She was discharged on February 9 after three negative nucleic acid tests.

Then she went home to rest, while taking care of her mother's mood, but also always worried about his father's situation. Her father told her to stay home when she got out of the hospital, and not to go to her mother's, to protect herself.

On February 12, she received a call from her doctor, who told her that her father's condition had worsened and that he had just been rescued. The doctor told her that her father's condition has been very critical, Chinese and Western medicine have been used, still no improvement. Li Yue had no choice but to be anxious and helpless.

By chance, she read in the news that 11 patients in Jiangxia District had been treated with plasma donated by patients recovering from new pneumonia. She immediately called her doctor and asked if she could donate plasma, and got a positive response.

A person's plasma can probably save two or three people, Zhang Dingyu, director of Wuhan's Jinyintan Hospital, told thepaper.cn. Plasma therapy does not guarantee 100 percent survival with a transfusion of plasma, but having plasma increases the chance of survival for critically ill patients and gives doctors time to treat them.

February 14, Li Yue resolutely rushed to the hospital. With no means of transportation and the community unable to arrange vehicles, she cycled six or seven kilometers to the hospital, just as she had when she left.

During the blood donation process, she was a little nervous, a side wearing protective clothing doctors kept comforting her and explaining, "0.01 second, 0.01 second of pain, just fine. "

The procedure went smoothly, and she was told that her plasma would need to be sent to a laboratory for testing for the virus, tested for antibodies after inactivation, and, if it worked, extracted and processed for final delivery to patients.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Yue donated plasma. Image from pear video clip

When she got home, she happily called her father and told him that she had donated plasma. She told him to hang in there for a few more days, and maybe there would be a cure for him soon, so they could visit their mother together.

On the other end of the line, my father was out of breath and could barely speak. Li Wasn't sure if her father had heard her encouragement.

Li knew it would take about seven days for the blood to be drawn and used to treat the patient. Her father's chances were slim, but she held out hope that he would persevere. "Even if my dad doesn't need it, other patients might, " she said

Let's hope it only lasted one night. At 8 am the next day, Li Yue received a phone call, his father was sent to the ICU for rescue; two hours later, another call, his father died.

There was no last face, no last words, so Li Yue "said goodbye" to his father.

All the paperwork was done on her phone, and she added a micro-signal called Hankou funeral home, and after sending out all the testimonials, her father's body was cremated that night.

February 15 that day, under the snow in Wuhan, the hospital let Li Yue go to the hospital as soon as possible to collect his father's belongings, but the bad weather coupled with sad mood, Li Yue has walked a step.

After a day's respite, she found an electric bike with the help of volunteers in Wuhan. Facing the sad rain and snow, she went to Jinyintan hospital again.

UNFINISHED GOOD-BYES

"I think she should know in her heart, because before my father would contact her, and now they haven't been in touch for a long time, " Ms. Li said tearfully, she hadn't told her mother that her father had died.

The mother had been trying to wean herself off the needles, but because her husband and daughter were being quarantined for infection, she had to hold out a little longer to see them again.

"I think it's also kind of selfish, " Ms. Li said, blaming herself. "We want her to hang on until we get out so we can walk her to the end. "

Shortly after Li made the donation, the mother's Hospital district was requisitioned to treat patients with new coronary pneumonia. The hospital nurse told her that there was a risk of cross-infection among the non-new-crown pneumonia patients who remained in the hospital and that her mother's care could not be as good as it had been because some of the staff had been transferred, so she was advised to bring her mother home.

But Li Yue just convalesces soon, also can not give the mother the injection at home, can only continue to leave her in the hospital. In the days that followed, the mother's nutrition needle was interrupted, and when Li Yue called her mother, her consciousness was not very clear.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo of interviewees in the ward where Li Yue's mother is staying

Desperate Li Yue one to a doctor and a nurse to call, are helpless response, other hospitals are unable to admit terminal cancer patients. At this time should be a week to replace the bag because of his father's death, has been two weeks no replacement, Li Yue is more anxious.

She had to beg people everywhere, and after several communications with the hospital, medical staff on February 17 late at night on the mother's pain injection.

On February 18, the latest news was released on the official website of the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission, which announced the list of medical treatment hospitals for special patients with non-new-crown pneumonia in the city. The hospital where Li Yue's mother was located was listed as a designated treatment hospital for malignant tumors, her nutrition needle was finally reapplied that same day.

However, the nurse told Li Yue that her mother's mental state was so bad that she could only speak Um um ah AH, and she was worried that her mother would not last long. She is still in quarantine, the community was closed, can not normal access, she even began to worry about whether to see her mother one last time.

On the morning of February 20, the doctor called Li Yue, because the mother's condition is very critical, the doctor confirmed to Li Yue, the mother signed not to resuscitate notice is still valid.

Endure grief, Li Yue expressed respect for the mother's will, let the mother safely away, she did not want her mother to suffer pain again. In the afternoon, the call came from the hospital -- as if she had lost her mother five days after her father had died.

That day, Li Yue took a chinese-style coat, white skirt and shoes and socks to the gate of the community. She had been told by her mother that they were her traveling clothes, and that she wanted to wear them when she died, as if she were on another trip.

However, Li Yue's aunt called, the old man in the phone crying to persuade her not to go to the hospital, the family has lost too much, she did not want Li Yue any more things. Although full of regret, Li Yue agreed, she left her mother's death to the nurse, and went home alone.

The House is still the same as it was before my parents left. Every morning, Li Yue would do exercises on the radio. After re-examination, she has no symptoms of new coronary pneumonia, but still cough, exercise to help her recover. She likes to cook. She'll be in a better mood.

When the thought of Random Thoughts strikes her, she watches TV and looks out the window. She advised herself not to think about the bad luck that had happened.

She said, her parents have left, she alone to take care of the body, which is the parents hope, but also close friends and relatives care. She was still waiting for the moment when the snow would stop, so that she could go out into the spring sunshine and say good-bye to her parents.
